Rascal is a CLI for starting, inspecting, and iterating autonomous coding runs on rascald.

Usage:
  rascal [flags]
  rascal [command]

Setup:
  auth        Authentication helpers
  bootstrap   Configure client, provision (optional), and deploy orchestrator
  config      Inspect effective config and manage local file values
  deploy      Deploy rascald to an existing host
  init        Initialize local Rascal CLI config

Runs:
  cancel      Cancel a queued or running run
  open        Open PR URL for a run in your browser
  ps          List recent runs
  retry       Create a new run from an existing run
  run         Start a run
  task        Show task status/details

Logs:
  logs        Fetch run/service logs

Integrations:
  github      GitHub integration setup and status
  infra       Infrastructure operations (provisioning/deploy)
  repo        Manage daemon repository registry and policies

Utilities:
  completion  Generate shell completion scripts
  doctor      Inspect local config and optional remote server readiness

Additional Commands:
  help        Help about any command

Flags:
      --api-token string         orchestrator API token
      --client-ssh-host string   SSH target host for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-key string    SSH private key path for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-port int      SSH target port for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-user string   SSH target user for API transport=ssh/auto
      --config string            config file path (default "$HOME/.rascal/config.toml")
      --default-repo string      default repository in OWNER/REPO form
      --env-file string          env file path (fallback: ./.rascal.env if present)
  -h, --help                     help for rascal
      --no-color                 disable ANSI color/style output (also set by NO_COLOR)
      --output string            output format: table|json|toml (default "table")
  -q, --quiet                    reduce non-essential output
      --server-url string        orchestrator URL
      --transport string         API transport: auto|http|ssh

Use "rascal [command] --help" for more information about a command.
